  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver pipeline incorporates custom Lagrangian particle-tracking modules, an in-house hemolysis integration library, and a parallelised MPI-based flow solver. Solver robustness was studied informally by the development team; no structured fault-injection, convergence-failure recovery, or numerical-stability boundary tests were performed. All validation runs completed to nominal termination without recorded exceptions.",
