      "name": "Steady-state hemolysis validation at 5000 RPM, 5 L/min",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index compared against FDA experimental measurements at 5000 RPM and 5 L/min. Solver completed to nominal termination. RH predicted = 0.87, measured = 0.91, relative error 4.4%. No solver exceptions recorded.",
      "outcome": "Accepted"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/gcbp-steady-state-3500rpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Steady-state hemolysis validation at 3500 RPM, 3 L/min",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index compared against FDA experimental measurements at 3500 RPM and 3 L/min. All five operating-point runs completed with nominal completion status. RH predicted = 0.72, measured = 0.76, relative error 5.3%. Solver robustness noted informally as satisfactory by the analyst without quantitative metrics.",
      "outcome": "Accepted"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/gcbp-mesh-independence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh independence study — three refinement levels",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (2.1M, 4.8M, 9.6M cells) evaluated for grid convergence index. All runs completed nominally. GCI between medium and fine meshes = 1.8%, below 5% threshold. No numerical instability or NaN events were reported; however no explicit fault-injection or stress testing of the solver was conducted at mesh boundaries or near-wall singularities.",
      "outcome": "Accepted"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/gcbp-particle-tracking-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Lagrangian particle-tracking code verification against analytical benchmark",
      "description": "Custom Lagrangian hemolysis integration library verified against analytical Stokes-flow particle trajectory benchmark. Nominal completion achieved across all 12 test trajectories. Maximum trajectory error 0.6%. Software fault modes such as race conditions in the MPI particle exchange routines, integer overflow in particle count arrays, or NaN propagation from zero-shear-rate cells were not exercised during verification.",
      "outcome": "Accepted"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/gcbp-turbulence-model-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence model sensitivity — SST k-omega vs. realizable k-epsilon",
      "description": "Two turbulence closures compared for the 5000 RPM operating point. Both models completed to nominal termination. SST k-omega selected as primary model based on 3.1% lower RH prediction error. No convergence-failure or divergence scenarios were tested; the assessment team noted informally that the solver appeared robust across the tested range.",
      "outcome": "Accepted"
    }
