    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model demonstrates adequate predictive accuracy for relative hemolysis index (RH) across the validated operating envelope, with maximum prediction error of 6.1% against the 10% acceptance criterion. Mesh independence, code verification, and model form sensitivity are adequately characterised. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The assessment team noted that solver robustness was reviewed informally and all validation runs completed to nominal termination, which was considered sufficient evidence of computational reliability for this risk level. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
